<subSubSection id="BE8AEB98FF97414EFF3C24F84E38FB8E" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F62FB813FF97414EFF3C24F84E38FB8E" blockId="13.[151,1436,968,1067]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="C4E46401FF97414EFF3C24F84B5EFC46" bold="true" box="[151,274,968,994]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3190C390FF97414EFEB324F84BE6FC46" authorityName="Sziraki" authorityYear="1998" box="[280,426,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Ascalohybris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4E46401FF97414EFEB324F84BE6FC46" box="[280,426,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Ascalohybris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="3190C390FF97414EFD7024F849A4FC46" authority="McLachlan" authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1873" box="[731,1000,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Glyptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4E46401FF97414EFD7024F8492DFC46" box="[731,865,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Glyptobasis</emphasis>
McLachlan
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3190C390FF97414EFBB524F94E86FC46" authority="Navas" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1923" box="[1054,1226,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Nousera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4E46401FF97414EFBB524F94E31FC46" box="[1054,1149,969,994]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Nousera</emphasis>
Navás
</taxonomicName>
by the lack of distinct triangular projection on the anal area in forewing and from all other split-eyed owlfly genera except 
<taxonomicName id="3190C390FF97414EFA9524DC4FD0FBA2" authorityName="Lefebvre" authorityYear="1842" box="[1342,1436,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Acheron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4E46401FF97414EFA9524DC4FD0FBA2" box="[1342,1436,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Acheron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of three rows of cells beyond Sc+R vein (
<bibRefCitation id="9201C5E2FF97414EFCB523204E4DFB8E" author="van der Weele, H. W." box="[798,1025,1040,1066]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref29095" refString="van der Weele, H. W. (1909) Ascalaphiden. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, Catalogue Systematique et Descriptif, 8, 1 - 326. [BotN ref  420]" type="journal article" year="1909">van der Weele 1909</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 184).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
